spgM3StripeShrink(25.10)                              spgM3StripeShrink(25.10)

Name
       spgM3StripeShrink

Syntax
        spgM3StripeShrink

       Specifies  the  shrink  effort  of the virtual M2 stripe by given total
       site units. This global should work with spgM3StripePushDown.

       If the default value is set to 0, it indicates that the  entire  pushed
       down  M3 stripe is used to evaluate M1 pin access. If the default value
       is set to more than 0, it indicates that M3 stripe will shrink  by  the
       specified  value  before  it  is  pushed down to M2. The left side will
       shrink first. For example, if the specified value is set to 1,  the  M3
       stripe will shrink by 1 site on left, and if the specified value is set
       to 2, 1 site on left will shrink, along with 1 site on right.

